# This file describes the installation of SpeciesGeoCoder on a Mac OSX or GNU/Linux system.
# The installation has been tested on the following systems + python versions:
Debian 6 (Squeeze) + python 2.6.6
Debian 7.5 (Wheezy) + python 2.7.3
Mac OSX 10.8.5 + python 2.7.5


# Dependencies*
Python module argparse (included in python v2.7) 
make
gcc

*The programs 'make' and 'gcc' are only needed if the pre-compiled versions of gdalinfo and gdallocationinfo does now work on your system. Both 'make' and 'gcc' should be installed on a regular GNU/Linux system. Mac OSX users can find installation istructions below.

# Notes about installing on Mac OSX.
'make' and 'gcc' are part of the package 'Xcode' that is available on Appstore. After installation, open Xcode, go to Preferences -> Downloads -> Components -> Command Line Tools, and install the commandline tools of Xcode.


### Installing using a web browser 
1). Direct your browser to the following URL (a compressed file will then be automatically downloaded):
https://github.com/mtop/speciesgeocoder/archive/master.zip

2). Unzip the file by clicking on it.
3). Open a terminal window and use the command "cd" and move into the directory "speciesgeocoder-master/"
4). Type 'make'
5). copy and paste the following command into your terminal window:
	./geocoder.py -l example_data/localities.csv -p example_data/polygons.txt -t example_data/*.tif


### Installing using wget
### Copy and paste the following commands in a terminal
wget https://github.com/mtop/speciesgeocoder/archive/master.zip
unzip master.zip
make
cd speciesgeocoder-master/
./geocoder.py -l example_data/localities.csv -p example_data/polygons.txt -t example_data/*.tif


### Installing using git
### Copy and paste the following commands in a terminal
git clone git@github.com:mtop/speciesgeocoder.git
cd speciesgeocoder/
make
./geocoder.py -l example_data/localities.csv -p example_data/polygons.txt -t example_data/*.tif





